quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  55,17,"Lord of the two Easts and the two Wests. (The East and the West of the summer, and the East and the West of the winter)"
  55,18,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,19,He has let free the two seas. They meet
  55,20,"Yet, there is a Barrier between them that they cannot exceed. (The great bodies of salt water and fresh water)"
  55,21,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,22,From both of them come forth pearl and coral
  55,23,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,24,And His are the bannered ships sailing through the sea lofty like mountains. (All creativity and invention of human beings issues forth from His gifts of mind and body. So all man-made things belong to Him)
  55,25,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,26,All things thereon (in the Universe) are ever changing. ('Fani' = Ever-changing = Mortal)
  55,27,"But forever is Changeless the 'Self' of your Lord, the Lord of Majesty and Honor. ('Baqi' = Remaining = Eternal = Survivor = Remainder = Changeless. 'Wajh' = Face = Countenance = Self = Whole being = Personality)"
  55,28,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,29,All creatures in the heavens and the earth seek their needs from Him. And every day is He in a Marvelous Splendor
  55,30,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,31,"Soon shall We lighten your burdens, O Burdened men and women"
  55,32,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,33,"O Communities of the rural and the urban! If you can break through the 'fences' of the heavens and the earth, then break through. Never can you break through without an Authority. Can you bring an evidence"
  55,34,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,35,"A blaze will be unleashed upon you - and thick smoke - and you will not be able to defend yourselves. (If you think that you can escape Divine Laws, you will never find your way in the thick smoke of conjecture)"
  55,36,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,37,And when the high elite will disperse and adapt to a stunning change
  55,38,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"
  55,39,In that Era neither the urban nor the rural will be asked why they trailed behind
  55,40,"Then, O Men and women! Which Authority of your Lord will you deny"